ted on nov 21 2011 the humboldt research award is the highest scientific honor of the alexander von humboldt foundation granted in recognition of a researcher's entire achievements to date to academics whose fundamental discoveries new theories or insights have had a significant impact on their own discipline and who are expected to continue producing cutting edge achievements in the future ishan nath earth systems named rhodes scholar for 2012 submitted on nov 20 2011 nath is pursuing a double major in economics and earth systems with a focus on energy and is one of five from stanford named rhodes scholars for 2012 noa lincoln phd candidate in e iper recognized as a 2011 ecological society of america education scholar submitted on nov 09 2011 lincoln was also appointed a contributing editor of the ecological society of america ecoed digital library pamela matson named to the einstein professorship of the chinese academy of sciences submitted on nov 09 2011 the award was presented on september 1 2011 by the institute of soil science chinese academy of sciences professor roland horne ere awarded the 2011 patricius plakette by the german geothermal association submitted on nov 03 2011 the award honors horne's significant work in the development of deep geothermal wells professor michael moldowan named 2011 treibs medalist submitted on sep 21 2011 the organic geochemistry division of the geochemical society has awarded the 2011 alfred treibs medal to j michael moldowan of stanford university the award will be presented at the 2011 imog meeting in interlaken switzerland professor paul segall geophysics to deliver william smith lecture the geological society london submitted on sep 19 2011 the annual lecture is named for william smith an english geologist credited with creating the first geological map of britain 1 2 3 4 next last stanford university school of earth sciences 397 panama mall ca 94305 2210 mitchell building 101 tel 650 723 2544 2012 stanford university rel